Full description at http://franchu.net/2008/01/08/interesting-ui-designs-in-museums/

While visiting the Nobel Peace Center in Oslo, Norway I found some interesting UIs in the museum. Virtual book controlled with IR LEDs a camera and a projector, displays that are conditioned to the presence of a person in front of them (ultrasound based), and physical sliding bars in a video wall made out of 19'' TFTs. Made by franchu.net. Music: Undercover by Nyx (CC)